            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Annual professional pitched roof inspection identifies developing issues before they cause damage. We recommend scheduling inspections in fall (September-October) before winter rains. Our comprehensive pitched roof inspection includes examining all roofing material for damage, cracks, or deterioration, checking valleys for debris accumulation or metal corrosion, inspecting flashing at chimneys, skylights, and penetrations, verifying ventilation system function and adequate airflow, examining soffits and fascias for damage or deterioration, checking gutters and downspouts for proper water drainage, and documenting roof condition with photos for your records. We also clean valleys and gutters removing debris that could impede drainage. Annual inspections cost $150-$350 depending on roof size and pitch (steep pitch requires more safety equipment). Many homeowners skip inspections until problems develop—this penny-wise-pound-foolish approach often results in $2,000-$8,000 repairs that $250 annual inspections would have prevented. We offer maintenance plans including annual inspections, priority emergency service, and repair discounts—learn about our [link:/services/family-protection-plans|Family Protection Plans] providing comprehensive home maintenance."
